---
/**
 * CDP Tools Guide - Internal Documentation
 *
 * Human-readable guide for the sales and marketing team on how to use
 * the CDP outcome tracking tools.
 */
import AdminLayout from '../../layouts/AdminLayout.astro'

const title = 'CDP Tools Guide | Admin'
---

<AdminLayout title={title}>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">CDP Tools Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
        How to use Southland's Customer Data Platform tools for tracking customer outcomes and
        improving marketing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Table of Contents -->
    <nav class="mb-12 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-lg font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">On This Page</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li>
          <a href="#overview" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">Overview: What is the CDP?</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#sales-log" class="text-green-600 hover:underline"
            >Sales Outcome Log (for Sales Team)</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#surveys" class="text-green-600 hover:underline"
            >Customer Outcome Surveys (for Marketing)</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#decision-engine" class="text-green-600 hover:underline"
            >Decision Engine (Homepage)</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#personas" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">Understanding Personas</a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="#faq" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">FAQ</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content Sections -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Overview Section -->
      <section id="overview" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Overview: What is the CDP?
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          The CDP (Customer Data Platform) helps us understand our customers better by tracking:
        </p>
        <ul class="mb-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-gray-600">
          <li><strong>Who they are</strong> ‚Äî Backyard Betty, Broiler Bill, or Turf Taylor</li>
          <li>
            <strong>What problems they're solving</strong> ‚Äî FCR improvement, mortality reduction, flock
            health
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>What results they're getting</strong> ‚Äî Real outcomes from using our products
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-6">
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-green-800">Why This Matters</h3>
          <p class="text-green-700">
            When we can prove our products work (with real data from real customers), we can: charge
            premium prices, win over skeptical buyers, and create better marketing.
            <strong>Proof points are our competitive moat.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Sales Log Section -->
      <section id="sales-log" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Sales Outcome Log
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          <strong>Who uses this:</strong> Sales team (Allen, Brad, Matt)
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-600">
          <strong>When to use:</strong> After any phone call where a customer shares results or places
          a reorder.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6 rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6">
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-amber-800">Why This Is Critical</h3>
          <p class="text-amber-700">
            34% of our revenue comes through phone orders ‚Äî and right now, we have NO DATA on those
            customers' outcomes. Every time a customer calls and says "my FCR improved by 3 points,"
            that's gold. We need to capture it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          How to Use the Sales Log
        </h3>

        <ol class="mb-6 list-decimal space-y-4 pl-6 text-gray-600">
          <li>
            <strong>Go to the Sales Log:</strong>
            <a href="/admin/sales-log" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">/admin/sales-log</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Fill in the call info:</strong> Your name, date, inbound/outbound
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Add customer details:</strong> Name, farm, email (if you have it), phone, operation
            type
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Select the outcome type:</strong>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li><strong>FCR Improvement</strong> ‚Äî Customer reported better feed conversion</li>
              <li><strong>Mortality Reduction</strong> ‚Äî Customer reported fewer bird losses</li>
              <li><strong>Reorder</strong> ‚Äî Customer placed an order (log the $ amount!)</li>
              <li><strong>Referral</strong> ‚Äî Customer referred another grower</li>
              <li><strong>Testimonial</strong> ‚Äî Customer willing to share their story</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Add specifics:</strong> If they gave you numbers (FCR went from 1.85 to 1.78), enter
            them!
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Submit:</strong> The data goes to our analytics system automatically.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 p-6">
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-blue-800">Pro Tips</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-blue-700">
            <li>
              Log outcomes <strong>immediately after the call</strong> while details are fresh
            </li>
            <li>
              Get email addresses when possible ‚Äî this helps us link phone customers to their online
              activity
            </li>
            <li>If a customer shares specific numbers, those are worth 10x vague feedback</li>
            <li>Mark "Testimonial Offered" whenever someone seems willing to share their story</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Surveys Section -->
      <section id="surveys" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Customer Outcome Surveys
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          <strong>Who manages this:</strong> Marketing team
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-600">
          <strong>How it works:</strong> Automated emails sent via Klaviyo at 30, 60, and 90 days after
          purchase.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">Two Survey Types</h3>

        <div class="mb-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6">
            <h4 class="mb-2 font-bold text-amber-800">Backyard Survey (Betty)</h4>
            <p class="mb-3 text-sm text-amber-700">
              <a href="/survey/backyard" class="underline">/survey/backyard</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-700">
              Asks about flock health, egg production, problem resolution. Simple 1-5 ratings and
              checkboxes. Takes ~2 minutes.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-6">
            <h4 class="mb-2 font-bold text-green-800">Commercial Survey (Bill)</h4>
            <p class="mb-3 text-sm text-green-700">
              <a href="/survey/commercial" class="underline">/survey/commercial</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-green-700">
              Asks about FCR, mortality, ROI, settlement impact. Collects actual numbers when
              possible. Takes ~4 minutes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Setting Up Klaviyo Flows
        </h3>

        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          To trigger surveys automatically, create Klaviyo flows with these settings:
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h4 class="mb-3 font-bold">Flow 1: 30-Day Post-Purchase (Betty)</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
            <li><strong>Trigger:</strong> Placed Order</li>
            <li><strong>Filter:</strong> Order contains "Backyard" product category</li>
            <li><strong>Delay:</strong> 30 days</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Email CTA Link:</strong>
              <code class="rounded bg-gray-200 px-2 py-1"
                >https://southlandorganics.com/survey/backyard?order_id=&#123;&#123;event.order_id&#125;&#125;&email=&#123;&#123;person.email&#125;&#125;</code
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <h4 class="mb-3 font-bold">Flow 2: 30-Day Post-Purchase (Bill)</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
            <li><strong>Trigger:</strong> Placed Order</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Filter:</strong> Order contains "Commercial" product category OR order value > $500
            </li>
            <li><strong>Delay:</strong> 30 days</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Email CTA Link:</strong>
              <code class="rounded bg-gray-200 px-2 py-1"
                >https://southlandorganics.com/survey/commercial?order_id=&#123;&#123;event.order_id&#125;&#125;&email=&#123;&#123;person.email&#125;&#125;</code
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Repeat for 60-day and 90-day flows. You can also create a one-time campaign to survey
          existing customers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Decision Engine Section -->
      <section id="decision-engine" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Decision Engine (Homepage)
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          <strong>What it is:</strong> The homepage now asks visitors "What best describes you?" and routes
          them to persona-specific landing pages.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-center">
            <div class="mb-2 text-2xl">üêî</div>
            <div class="font-bold text-amber-800">Backyard Flock</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-amber-600">‚Üí /poultry/backyard/</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-green-50 p-4 text-center">
            <div class="mb-2 text-2xl">üè†</div>
            <div class="font-bold text-green-800">Commercial Poultry</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-green-600">‚Üí /poultry/commercial/</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-emerald-50 p-4 text-center">
            <div class="mb-2 text-2xl">üå±</div>
            <div class="font-bold text-emerald-800">Lawn & Garden</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-emerald-600">‚Üí /lawn/</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600">
          <strong>How it works:</strong>
        </p>
        <ol class="mb-6 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 text-gray-600">
          <li>Visitor clicks their persona</li>
          <li>Choice is saved in a cookie (persists for 1 year)</li>
          <li>Event fires to analytics (persona_path_selected)</li>
          <li>Visitor is redirected to their persona landing page</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="text-gray-600">
          <strong>Future enhancement:</strong> Returning visitors will see personalized content throughout
          the site based on their stored persona.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Personas Section -->
      <section id="personas" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Understanding Our Personas
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-amber-800">Backyard Betty (42% of customers)</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-amber-700">
              <li><strong>Who:</strong> Hobby chicken keepers, 5-50 birds at home</li>
              <li><strong>Avg LTV:</strong> $77</li>
              <li><strong>Buys:</strong> Small quantities, values "safe & natural"</li>
              <li><strong>Outcome we track:</strong> Flock health improvement, egg production</li>
              <li><strong>How she shops:</strong> Mostly online, reads reviews</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-green-800">Broiler Bill (44% of customers)</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-green-700">
              <li><strong>Who:</strong> Commercial poultry farmers, contract growers</li>
              <li><strong>Avg LTV:</strong> $903</li>
              <li><strong>Buys:</strong> Bulk quantities, needs proven ROI</li>
              <li><strong>Outcome we track:</strong> FCR improvement, mortality reduction</li>
              <li><strong>How he shops:</strong> 34% by phone, wants to talk to a human</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-emerald-800">
              Turf Pro Taylor (8% of customers)
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 text-emerald-700">
              <li><strong>Who:</strong> Lawn care enthusiasts, landscapers</li>
              <li><strong>Buys:</strong> Soil amendments, organic lawn products</li>
              <li><strong>Outcome we track:</strong> Lawn health improvement</li>
              <li><strong>How she shops:</strong> Online, seasonal buying patterns</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <section id="faq" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">
          Frequently Asked Questions
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-gray-900">Where does the data go?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              All data flows to BigQuery (our data warehouse) where it's combined with Shopify
              orders, website analytics, and email engagement to build a complete picture of each
              customer.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-gray-900">How do I see the results?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Dashboards coming soon. For now, ask Mike or check the BigQuery console if you have
              access.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-gray-900">
              What if a customer doesn't want to fill out a survey?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              That's fine ‚Äî surveys are optional. But if you're on the phone and they share results,
              log it in the Sales Outcome Log. Every data point helps.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-gray-900">
              Can I see what persona a specific customer is?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Not yet in a user-friendly way. This is coming. For now, you can infer from their
              purchase history (commercial products = Bill, backyard products = Betty).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 font-bold text-gray-900">
              What should I do if I find a great testimonial candidate?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Mark "Testimonial Offered" in the Sales Log, add their contact info, and let Marketing
              know. We'll follow up to get a proper case study.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Quick Links -->
      <section class="rounded-xl bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold" style="color: var(--color-title);">Quick Links</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <a
            href="/admin/sales-log"
            class="block rounded-lg bg-white p-4 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"
          >
            <span class="font-semibold text-green-600">Sales Outcome Log ‚Üí</span>
            <span class="block text-sm text-gray-500">Log phone call outcomes</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="/survey/backyard"
            class="block rounded-lg bg-white p-4 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"
          >
            <span class="font-semibold text-green-600">Backyard Survey ‚Üí</span>
            <span class="block text-sm text-gray-500">Preview Betty's survey</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="/survey/commercial"
            class="block rounded-lg bg-white p-4 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md"
          >
            <span class="font-semibold text-green-600">Commercial Survey ‚Üí</span>
            <span class="block text-sm text-gray-500">Preview Bill's survey</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/" class="block rounded-lg bg-white p-4 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md">
            <span class="font-semibold text-green-600">Homepage (Decision Engine) ‚Üí</span>
            <span class="block text-sm text-gray-500">See the persona selector</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</AdminLayout>
